<task id="106" project="spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>PCF v1.1.75: drop bound `searchIndexName`; add `resolveSearchIndexNameAsync` via `context.webAPI`; 5-location version bump</title>
    <phase>G: Lookup-driven multi-index</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>3-4</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>100</dependencies>
    <blocks>107</blocks>
    <tags>pcf, frontend, manifest</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Tags include `pcf`; modifies `.tsx` manifest + main control file; manifest contract change (bound property removed). 5-location version bump must be exact. Code-review + adr-check at Step 9.5.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>G3</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Client-side; disjoint from BFF resolver work in 102. Both consume the lookup column from task 100.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Update `SemanticSearchControl` PCF to v1.1.75. (1) Remove `searchIndexName` `&lt;property&gt;` element from `ControlManifest.Input.xml` (it's no longer a bound property). (2) Add `resolveSearchIndexNameAsync(context)` method that uses `context.webAPI.retrieveRecord(entityType, entityId, '?$select=_sprk_aisearchindexid_value&amp;$expand=sprk_aisearchindexid($select=sprk_searchindexname)')` to read the host record's lookup expansion. (3) Wire the resolved value into the existing `boundSearchIndexName` consumption sites (search hook + URL envelope builder) — downstream is unchanged. (4) Version bump in 5 locations per `.claude/skills/pcf-deploy/SKILL.md`.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    PCF developer familiar with `src/client/pcf/SemanticSearchControl/`, Spaarke Auth v2 (`@spaarke/auth`), ADR-022 (PCF stays React 16, no React 18 APIs), and the canonical 5-location PCF version-bump pattern.
  </role>

  <goal>
    PCF v1.1.75 manifest has no `searchIndexName` bound property; the control resolves the index name itself via `context.webAPI` lookup expansion on init. All downstream consumption (URL envelope + search calls) reads the resolved value identically to v1.1.74. Backward compatible with the BFF (string wire format unchanged).
  </goal>

  <context>
